**Exploring my fascination with Web3 and Runescape.**  
I quite often get asked by people outside of the Crypto vortex, how I got into Web3. My answer? I played Runescape.  
---

# **Starting Out..**

I graduated and wanted to work in Communications. That, I knew. But after 6 years of study, work, observation and trial it felt like web2 marketing and communications work was losing it’s ***colour***, ***creativity*** and ***innovation***. Slowly but surely, the life was being drained from it as media & tech squeezed tired web2 business models dry. It all seemed utterly uninspiring. I needed to look elsewhere.

Enter, “Web3”*.* Rapidly gaining mindshare & still in its infancy. The new kid on the block ***looked*** and ***felt*** different \- particularly to me and others who spend a lot of their time online. To us, it’s a ready made fascination.

![The old Runescape Login Screen.][./images/runescapelogin.jpg]

The old Runescape Login Screen.

The fascination was rooted in the ***scope of ideas*** and the ***speed*** at which others in *Web3* were sharing and building. That fascination, as it turned out, attracted a lot of like-minded people. Myself included. It was eye opening and I think *Runescape* has a lot to do with it.

I often joke with people the Venn diagram of people who played *Runescape* in the 2000’s and people who are now full time in Crypto is a ***complete circle***. Having been in the space for past 3 years, anecdotally, it seems true.

![Source: Me][./images/venndiagram.jpg]

Source: Me

---

# **Making the connection..**

The pandemic brought about a ***MASSIVE*** shift in online behavior. People (me) suddenly had time to explore new digital spaces.

That entire two year period felt like hundreds, even thousands of different internet cultures had become actualized and eventually coalesced, creating a network big enough to play a ***real life, real-time, networked*** ***metagame***.

Incidentally, I think that is one of the *best* ways to conceptualize Web3. It’s a world-wide metagame facilitated by blockchain, which has formed the ***framework*** \- and the ***network*** \- required for players & communities to ***expand outwardly***, creating a larger real-world game where the same skills apply.

Ok.. so? What does that matter?

![Wage slave, coom & game until you die. Or participate in Web3 causing wide spread disruption re-engineer government & perhaps become filthy rich in the process. The choice is yours, Western Man.][./images/runescapeandweb3.jpg]

Wage slave, coom & game until you die. Or participate in Web3 causing wide spread disruption re-engineer government & perhaps become filthy rich in the process. The choice is yours, Western Man.

The Web3 metagame is ***plugged into*** and ***disrupting*** the real world in big ways. That sense of excitement and promise you get from discovering a new game \- the sense of ***disruption*** \- is all it takes to get you hooked.

That’s why it’s so compelling. It’s a game you feel a **NEED** to play.. a game capable of being all encompassing; a ***source of income*** and perhaps even a ***career***. Like *Runescape*, web3 is an endless sprawling adventure. You choose your own destiny and forge your own adventure within a new virtual economy. It’s a mind blowing learning experience, intertwined with ***state craft, economics, politics, psychology*** & ***money***.

The *Runescape* players had already been primed to understand (at least at a very basic level) most of what is required to play the larger Web3 game. It’s an ***adventure***, just waiting for you to start.

![The Runescape Map. Source: Oldschool Runescape Wiki][./images/therunescapemap.jpg]

The Runescape Map. Source: Oldschool Runescape Wiki

The thing about this adventure, is that it’s a fucking ***MASSIVE*** time sink. The learning curve is ***steep*** and the knowledge required and acquired when playing is ***vast***. Most people don’t have the time. Enter; ***COVID***. The perfect opportunity to play & learn uninterrupted. An opportunity for ***2 year long COVID*** holiday, playing and learning Web3.

![The Web3 Stack. “A Map, or navigation of the infrastructure, apps and tools in Web3” Source: MapDAO Discord.][./images/image5]

The Web3 Stack. “A Map, or navigation of the infrastructure, apps and tools in Web3” Source: MapDAO Discord.

Like most great games, it ***expands your mind*** and ***reveals more*** as you play. The power of a global network and its implications for a financially and politically compartmentalized world slowly dawns on you as you progress.

An anon moderator in a Discord group helps you mint your first *NFT’**s.*** You sell an *NFT* to someone in Nigeria and stake your profits in a dApp whose developers come from ***5 different continents***. You now ***earn interest*** and ***facilitate trades*** by becoming a ***liquidity provider***. The developers of this dApp work through timezones in multiple languages building a ***neobank*** capable of functioning as a ***permission-less financial system***. You realize while playing what you’re doing is the very beginning of something genuinely novel; The construction of new, ***borderless online economies*** capable of encompassing the ***whole world***. And you’re right there in the thick of it; a vital cog in a machine being built from the ground up. You’ve opted into this economy just like you did *Runescape*. You’re adventuring. Finding new places, faster routes, cheaper trades, honing skills and new weird & wonderful people. Discovering, unearthing and creating in un-chartered, unknown territory. And it’s fucking **THRILLING**.

![Stop rent seeking middle men & arbitrary borders from infringing on progress with one simple trick Smart Contract. Monopolies hate him.][./images/web2vsweb3.jpg]

Stop rent seeking middle men & arbitrary borders from infringing on progress with one simple trick Smart Contract. Monopolies hate him.

# **Now you’re hooked.**

So that’s how I found myself working in Web3. Playing the game. And that’s where I think people’s fascination for it stems from. The sense of adventure.

It’s the understanding that you’re able to explore and create new and evolving economies that are capable of things people never dreamed of. You play for stakes ***exponentially*** larger than any video game. You, the humble person with a laptop, can engineer new economies and financial systems from the ground up. Just like you once dreamt you were doing in *Runescape*.

Working full time in Web3 is what making it feels like, to me. I get to play a game I adore and also earn a living. *The adventure has only just begun for people like me.*

There is a ‘***but..***’ to this realization, though. This adventure has an ***expiry date***.

That ‘feeling’ *Runescape* once had eventually ***wore off***. Just about everything to discover and do had been done, documented and recorded. This will also happen in Web3, eventually. So I’m determined to ***enjoy it while it lasts***. These are the good old days.

Cheers,

Choppa.
